Job Summary/Overview
The Software Support Specialist position will provide our new hire with a uniquely experiential opportunity to immerse themselves in the day-to-day bustle of a prestigious legal group’s Finance Software Development Department. Our firm maintains a collegial work environment that prioritizes internal promotion, training, and professional development. We strive to see our employees grow! As our team-members progress and demonstrate a consistent ability to meet performance standards, promotional opportunities become available.

Essential Duties and Responsibilities
Create and maintain dynamic Legal Documents according to our in-house Attorneys’ preferences;
Automate the creation of Legal Documents in order to increase staff production as much as possible while reducing margin for human error;
Assist with assigning development tasks, providing first level Application Support for our in-house Content Management System (CMS), and escalating issues to Development Team as needed;
Troubleshoot problems within our in-house software;
Participate in special projects as assigned by management;
Assist with ticketing system triggered by end users.

Full-time (40 hr./week) position

Qualifications
Required Knowledge, Skills and Abilities:
Great troubleshooting and logical/critical thinking skills;
Intermediate to advanced-level computer and general office skills; Strong interpersonal skills;
Ability to effectively communicate verbally and through written electronic correspondence;
Demonstrated ability to analyze corrective action opportunities and present recommendations;
Knowledge of SQL to assist with Merge documentation;
Customer Service skills.
Experience (Preferred):
Very light SQL knowledge such as writing Select statements
Understanding of Boolean statements
Light knowledge of HTML

